article.headline: South Alabama 73, Denver 54
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Chris Young and Malerick Bedden snapped out of late-season scoring slumps to combine for 35 points and help South Alabama to a 73-54 victory over Denver Thursday night. It was the second straight win for the Jaguars (11-15, 5-9 Sun Belt Conference). Young hit four 3-pointers to finish with 18 points. Bedden scored 17 points. Denver (14-12, 6-8) trailed 15-14 with 11:27 remaining in the first, but South Alabama rallied for a 14-4 run to lead 29-18 with 6:06 left. The Pioneers ended the half trailing 37-29. South Alabama came back to shoot 61 percent from the floor and stretched the lead to 49-31. Denver came within 13 points on two occasions in the second, but South Alabama led 73-48 with 2:22 left. Yemi Nicholson lead Denver with 18 points, while Richard Law and Henry Williams each added nine.
